  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a color with red, green, blue, and alpha components, packed as a BGRA value.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

<xref:T:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor> stores a color as a 32-bit BGRA value where Blue occupies the most-significant byte and Alpha occupies the least-significant byte (`0xBBGGRRAA`).

To convert between <xref:T:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor> and <xref:T:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, use the extension methods in <xref:T:SkiaSharp.HarfBuzz.ColorExtensions>.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create a fully-opaque red color
var red = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 0, blue: 0, alpha: 255);

// Convert to/from uint
uint packed = red;           // implicit
var restored = (HBColor)packed;  // explicit cast
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
